itemListElement.name: Seabrook Washington Exclusive Private Explore the Shore

name: Seabrook Washington Exclusive Private Explore the Shore
description: A day trip from Seattle to Seabrook, WA takes you through a journey of diverse landscapes. As you drive south, you'll pass the Nisqually Wildlife Preserve, where the wetlands and wildlife hint at the area's natural beauty. Continue past Aberdeen, known for its industrial history, and catch sight of the eerie, unfinished Satsop Nuclear Power Plant, with its towering cooling structures looming in the distance. Finally, you’ll reach Seabrook, a charming coastal town where you can relax, walk the beach, and explore the peaceful surroundings, all before heading back along the same scenic route.

itemListElement.name: Mt. Rainier National Park Private Tour

name: Mt. Rainier National Park Private Tour
description:
A special private group tour of majestic Mt. Rainier National Park, one of the finest parks in the country! 

We offer specialty chocolate bars and good snacks. 

This is not a typical crowded van tour experience but a comfortable and pleasant experience. It will be a more personal and comfortable day on Mt. Rainier. 

Mt. Rainier is an active volcano, meaning it will likely erupt some day, but not on the day of your tour!

We will decide which parts of the mountain most interest you.

We can drive up to Paradise Lodge (5,400 ft elevation) and take a hike to explore the surrounding area and take in the view.

Other stops include:
Reflection Lakes,
Narada Waterfalls
Christine Waterfalls
Twin Firs trail 

We will make a food and rest stop at a national historic town called Elbe, which has specially painted old train that runs on the weekends.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Beer Wander - Ballard Brewery District

name: Seattle Beer Wander - Ballard Brewery District
description:
Walk through a neighborhood where there is a brewery on every block. With visits to at least five of the 20+ breweries in the area, this tour offers insights into the brewing process and the reasons behind Seattle's brewery boom. Enjoy personalized attention from your guide in a small group setting, making it perfect for beer enthusiasts looking to deepen their appreciation of local brews. On this tour, you’ll sample many classic and unique beer styles. Get a taste of the history of Seattle's craft beer scene and experience how alive and well it is today. 
If you're a beer lover and visiting Seattle, don't miss this tour!

- Explore the Ballard Brewery District with over 20 breweries
- Sample classic and unique beer styles at five local breweries
- Learn about Seattle's craft beer history and brewing process
- Enjoy a small group experience for personalized attention

review.name: Ballard Beer Tasting
review.reviewBody: James was a great guide and would highly recommend. James was funny, highly knowledgeable and gave great insight at each location.

name: Hands On Cocktail Making Workshop
description:
In the first part of your cocktail making journey you will learn about spirits, tools and techniques needed to successfully execute a tasty libation.
 Then you will prepare your first cocktail using your favorite spirit. This is where you warm up those shaking arms, and try not to laugh at yourself and others while you shake a cocktail as hard as you can 
With a cocktail in your hand, you will learn how to modify and create new cocktails using your base cocktail recipe.
In the next step you will get creative with a professional bartender in your corner to guide you, as you pick out the ingredients to shake up a cocktail with your own touch and flavor.
Before you realize you have created your own unique libation utilizing everything you have learned at the workshop.
With all the techniques, tools, history, recipes and pro tips and tricks you can confidently entertain and impress guests at your own home.
